{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C3771 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3771 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"pos":[619,639],"content":"Compiler Error C3771","linkify":"Compiler Error C3771","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3771","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"\"identifier\" : friend declaration cannot be found in the nearest namespace scope","pos":[640,720]},{"pos":[726,842],"content":"The class template declaration for the specified template <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>identifier<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> cannot be found within the current namespace.","source":"The class template declaration for the specified template *identifier* cannot be found within the current namespace."},{"pos":[852,873],"content":"To correct this error","linkify":"To correct this error","nodes":[{"content":"To correct this error","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"Ensure that the class template declaration for the template identifier is defined in the current namespace or that the template identifier is a fully-qualified name.","pos":[883,1048]},{"pos":[1057,1064],"content":"Example","linkify":"Example","nodes":[{"content":"Example","pos":[0,7]}]},{"pos":[1067,1221],"content":"The following code example declares a class template and function in namespace <ph id=\"ph1\">`NA`</ph>, but attempts to declare a friend function template in namespace <ph id=\"ph2\">`NB`</ph>.","source":"The following code example declares a class template and function in namespace `NA`, but attempts to declare a friend function template in namespace `NB`."},{"pos":[1662,1670],"content":"See Also","linkify":"See Also","nodes":[{"content":"See Also","pos":[0,8]}]},{"pos":[1673,1712],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Templates<ept id=\"p1\">](../../cpp/templates-cpp.md)</ept>","source":"[Templates](../../cpp/templates-cpp.md)"}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C3771 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-csharp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C3771\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C3771\"\nms.assetid: 68c23b25-7f21-4eaa-8f7e-38fda1130a69\ncaps.latest.revision: 12\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\ntranslation.priority.mt: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C3771\n\"identifier\" : friend declaration cannot be found in the nearest namespace scope  \n  \nThe class template declaration for the specified template *identifier* cannot be found within the current namespace.  \n  \n### To correct this error  \n  \n-   Ensure that the class template declaration for the template identifier is defined in the current namespace or that the template identifier is a fully-qualified name.  \n  \n## Example  \nThe following code example declares a class template and function in namespace `NA`, but attempts to declare a friend function template in namespace `NB`.  \n  \n```cpp  \n// C3771.cpp   \n// compile with: /c  \n  \nnamespace NA {  \ntemplate<class T> class A {  \n    void aFunction(T t) {};  \n    };  \n}  \n// using namespace NA;  \nnamespace NB {  \n    class X {  \n        template<class T> friend void A<T>::aFunction(T); // C3771  \n// try the following line instead  \n//      template<class T> friend void NA::A<T>::aFunction(T);  \n// or try \"using namespace NA;\" instead.  \n    };  \n}  \n```  \n  \n## See Also  \n[Templates](../../cpp/templates-cpp.md)  "}